# 3. 友達

Kanade: *Sigh*
Kanade: (Starting today, I'm a third-year...)
Kanade: (It's nice that I'm in the same class as my two closest friends again, but I haven't talked to most of the others.)
Kanade: (I'm a little nervous...)
Kanade: (But I can't just stand here staring at my feet forever.)
Kanade: I should start by greeting everyone...
Kanade: G-Good morning...
Classmate A: Morning, Kanade! I'm so glad we're in the same class again!
Classmate B: Let's make this year another great one.
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Y-Yes, let's do just that...!
Kanade: Thank goodness. I feel so much better knowing that you two are here.
Classmate A: Haha. It's pretty awkward when you're surrounded by a bunch of unfamiliar faces, huh. I'm glad we're together again too!
Classmate C: I'm so glad that we're in the same class again this year, Mafuyu! Let's have lots of fun together!
Kanade: (Mafuyu...?)
Mafuyu: I'm also looking forward to this upcoming year. But you need to make an effort to do your homework on your own, okay?
Classmate C: I know! I will!
Kanade: (I'm in the same class as Asahina...)
Mafuyu: Good morning, Yoisaki.
Mafuyu: What a surprise to see we're in the same class.
Kanade: Y-Yes, I'm surprised as well...
Kanade: But I'm also a little happy. I was hoping to get to know you a little better.
Mafuyu: Hehe. Me too.
Mafuyu: I look forward to being your classmate.
Kanade: This part needs to have more of a skip to its step...
Kanade: Okay, this sounds good. Now, the next part should give the listener a sense of clarity...
???: ♪———— ♪————...
Kanade: Huh? Was someone singing just now...?
Kanade: Or did I just imagine that?
Kanade: (But that gentle voice sounded so real.)
Kanade: Hmm, for that feeling I just had...
Kanade's Father's Voice: Kanade, can I come in?
Kanade: Oh... Yes!
Kanade's Father: I thought we could have dinner soon. Do you have any requests?
Kanade: It's already that late? I'm sorry. I completely forgot...
Kanade's Father: No, that's okay. I finished working early today.
Kanade's Father: Also...
Kanade's Father: Your music sounds like you're having more fun than usual today, so I didn't want to interrupt your work.
Kanade: Huh? Oh...
Kanade: W-Was it really coming through that clearly?
Kanade's Father: Yes, your music was especially bouncy.
Kanade's Father: Did something good happen today?
Kanade: Yes...
Kanade: We were assigned to new classes today, and I'm in the same class as a girl I've been wanting to talk to for a while now.
Kanade: I feel like maybe we could be friends.
Kanade's Father: I see...
Kanade's Father: That's a nice twist of fate.
Kanade: It is...!
Classmate A: Kanade! You uploaded that new song last night, right?! It's so good!
Classmate B: You came up with another really fun song. I got all excited just listening to it.
Kanade: Thank you. I got to work on it the second I got home, so I was worried it might feel a little rushed...
Kanade: But I'm glad you both like it so much.
Classmate A: What?! You made it that fast?!
Classmate B: You really are amazing... You make such good music, and so fast too.
Kanade: I-I'm really nothing special...
Mafuyu: Hehe. You three seem to be having fun.
Classmate A: Oh, Asahina, you gotta listen to this! Kanade's new song is really awesome!
Mafuyu: Oh, Yoisaki, you write your own songs?
Kanade: Y-Yes, I do...
Classmate A: Kanade's really amazing! She posts her songs online as “K”, and she's super popular!
Mafuyu: Really now? I do like listening to music, so I'd love to hear it.
Mafuyu: Could I, Yoisaki?
Kanade: Of course...! Um, this is my latest one...
Mafuyu: Thank you.
Kanade: ...?
Mafuyu: *Nod* It's very nice.
Mafuyu: I'm feeling more cheerful already.
Kanade: Huh...?
Classmate A: I know, right?! I really like this other one too! Give it a listen!
Mafuyu: Hehe. I can't wait to hear it.
